Yag. Just trying to find a way to make a mostly useless spell more useful. And it would prolly be a spell with limited uses but if changed would definitely be memmed more than it is now. Very situational, but more useful at the level necros recieve it.

Some really kickass suggestions on improving this spell to make it more usefull than it is at this moment in time. And isnt that how shit gets changed in the first place? Kick around a few ideas, present it in a way that the developers might actually take a look at and maybe, just maybe the spell, item, skill, whatever just might get changed. Stanger stuff has happened.

And those that mentioned the spell fill the persons or targets mana pool, maybe an upgrade to this spell? Would be quite powerful so maybe a new spell 63+? Because at the level this spell in introduced to the players arsenal (55), 1000 mana is quite good IMO. But like Num said, targetable full mana restoration, 60 minute reuse time for the cost of an EE is pretty damn resonable. Especially at higher levels.

But yall need to remember, this a level 55 spell, so if it were to be changed necros that level and a few above would find more uses for it than lvl 65 necs with 100+ AAs. That was what I was aiming, making it more usefull for the level it is recieved and a few above where 1000 extra mana would and can make a difference in any number of scenerios.

Still, some real kick ass suggestions yall. Thanks for the input.

PS: If this response seem incoherent and hard to follow, I blame recreation abuse of certain mind altering substances. /grins


Bohica
